We are carrying out these works to upgrade a piece of equipment known as a pole transformer to enable new services to be connected to the overhead electricity network. This work is following on from a customer's request and to ensure engineers can carry out this work safely will need to temporarily switch off your power. This work will ensure the electricity network can uphold the amount of electricity required for the area. During this time you will be connected to a generator to provide you electricity whilst we carry out our essential works. We aim to connect and disconnect the generator within 15 minutes so your power may come on sooner. This work is taking place in the Woodhill Lane area.

They will also be replacing and upgrading some overhead electricity cables with improved insulated cables. This will improve the reliability of our electricity network and reduce the risk of you having an unplanned power cut. You may see our contractors erecting the new electricity poles prior to the outage to allow for a shorter interruption. This work is taking place outside 87 The Quarries up to 45 The Quarries. This will also reduce the possibility of you having an unplanned power cut by stopping these trees from potentially causing damage to our overhead electricity network. This is why it is important to complete this during the Coronavirus pandemic. This work is taking place on Kithurst Lane.
